President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences on the passing of Gordie Howe, a legendary hockey player. He highlighted how Howe's career spanned six decades, making him the only player to achieve this feat. Obama also mentioned Howe's impact on aspiring young players who looked up to him and dreamed of emulating his success. Howe's success on the ice and his representation of Detroit were also highlighted, with mention of his four championships and multiple All-Star appearances. The statement ended with Obama and his wife Michelle sending their condolences to Howe's family and fans across North America.